      "content": "I understand you're desperate for relief, but taking aspirin or additional ibuprofen without proper guidance can still be dangerous. Aspirin can thin your blood, increasing the risk of bleeding, especially if you're taking ibuprofen, which also affects blood clotting. It's not advisable to self-medicate in this way. Instead, try some gentle stretches, apply a warm compress, or use over-the-counter pain relief that's safe for you to take. If the pain continues, consider visiting an urgent care clinic or emergency room in the morning when it's safer to drive. Your health is important, and it's better to err on the side of caution.",
